    {
      "id": "e0ed551bf3fe14f10c2d5749198b4ba470f2c272",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 626,
        "name": "Quentin Bouget",
        "email": "quentin.bouget@cea.fr",
        "username": "bougetq"
      },
      "date": "2017-06-14 11:10:18.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nI personnaly think it is the second option, and we should simply replace:\n\n\"ma->ma_valid = 0\" with \"ma->ma_valid ~= ~need\" in mdt_attr_get_complex()\n\nor possibly do it after each \"if (need & MA_XXX) {\":\n\nif (need & MA_INODE) {\n    ma->ma_valid ~= MA_INODE;\n    ...\n}\n\nto limit invalidation to the minimum in case of an error.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "3dad1a2352f7ba1c4ccf22e14b0691d2d1c438f0",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 337,
        "name": "Li Xi",
        "email": "lixi@ddn.com",
        "username": "LiX"
      },
      "date": "2017-06-22 01:57:40.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nQuentin,\n\nI have the same questions about mdt_attr_get_complex(). And I agree we need to change it, but that should be in a seperate patch. mdt_attr_get_complex() is being used by so many functions, which brings my concern that if we change the functions, something might broken.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "3ce9607f48fdb26c8373eac9ab3031dc708fe3f9",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 337,
        "name": "Li Xi",
        "email": "lixi@ddn.com",
        "username": "LiX"
      },
      "date": "2017-06-22 01:58:00.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nPing reviewers",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "7bbce3c4f3bda17c8088073f3b7a9507d180ee9a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 626,
        "name": "Quentin Bouget",
        "email": "quentin.bouget@cea.fr",
        "username": "bougetq"
      },
      "date": "2017-06-22 11:31:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nI opened LU-9702 about mdt_attr_get_complex(). If the problem is confirmed, I don't see the point in merging this patch instead of directly fixing mdt_attr_get_complex().",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "19dae47732654793938c896219da30c49f9a6440",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 337,
        "name": "Li Xi",
        "email": "lixi@ddn.com",
        "username": "LiX"
      },
      "date": "2017-06-27 07:03:13.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nQuentin, I totally agree to investigate the behavoir of mdt_attr_get_complex(). But can we please go on reviewing this patch rather than waiting LU-9702. LU-9702 might need months before being closed. And the problem that this patch is trying to fix is too cirtical to wait for LU-9702. Without it, RAoLU can't be used at all at least for some version.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "4fed016092633accb9895e977532f21146c4b95c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 626,
        "name": "Quentin Bouget",
        "email": "quentin.bouget@cea.fr",
        "username": "bougetq"
      },
      "date": "2017-06-27 07:38:27.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nWell... I still don't like it... But I don't think see any structural problem with the patch.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
